children.subject: Second year, passionate about education - very interested!

history.content:
Every year we invite high school students from around the Bay Area to come and experience a little bit of the flavor of our department. This year, we are working together with Microsoft's volunteer branch, TEALS, to put on our traditional CS Ed Day.

We are running panels in the Woz, and for one of the panels, we want to have one undergrad and one transfer student from a community college to speak with Christopher Hunn and a faculty member about their experiences with EECS. The panel will run twice between 10 and 3 to audiences of a little over 200 high school students each time.

If you are an undergrad or a transfer student from a community college and would like to sit on this panel (which would look great on your resume!), please let me know.

Thank you!

Heather 

EECS Undergrad Advisor & Programs Coordinator
